   <body>
      <p>The <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol> is a repository of all fund sources that  are available to all projects in the enterprise. You can use the list of approved global fund sources for fund reporting in projects.</p>
      <p>The fund source records are automatically created through data integration.</p>
      <p>In a scenario where the transaction is done in EBS for the Fund Number
that is not available in Mind, a new Global Fund should be created and
approved by the user (Fund Manager).</p>
      <p>The functional flow for global fund management (manual creation) is as follows:<ol>
            <li>Global Fund List<ol>
                  <li>
                     <xref href="DefineGFSources.xml">Create a global fund source</xref>
                  </li>
                  <li product="Include_PG_Content">
                     <xref href="Approving_a_Global_Fund_Source_Record.xml"/>
                  </li>
                  <li product="Exclude_PG_Content">
                     <xref href="GFSourceWF.xml">Perform workflow actions to implement the business process for fund sources</xref>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </p>
      <p>You can activate or deactivate a fund source at any point in time. By default, only the active records are displayed in the <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol> page.<ul product="Exclude_PG_Content">
            <li>
               <p>To view and activate an inactive fund source, refer to <xref href="Activating_a_Global_Fund_List_Record.xml">Activating a Global Fund List Record</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p>To deactivate a fund source, refer to <xref href="Deaca_Glob_Fund_List_Rec.xml">Deactivating a Global Fund List Record</xref>. </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
